---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { INSTAGRAM_URL } from '../config';
---

<BaseLayout title="Join Us">
  <section class="section page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Join Us</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Become a part of our bird watching community.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section join-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <h2>Who Can Participate</h2>
        <p>We warmly welcome anyone with a love for nature, from veteran birders eager to share their knowledge to absolute beginners taking their very first steps into bird watching. You do not need expensive equipment (such as high-end cameras or spotting scopes) or prior expertise to start—just a sense of wonder and curiosity.</p>
        
        <div class="sub-section">
          <h3>Educational Workshops for Children</h3>
          <p>In addition to our public community walks, we design and conduct introductory birding workshops specifically tailored for children from educational institutions (schools, colleges, and youth groups). These full-day, immersive programs feature guided birdwalks, interactive workshops, and fun, observation-based nature activities to inspire the next generation of environmental stewards.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Our Walk Schedule</h2>
        <p>To help you plan your schedule ahead of time, <strong>we commit to hosting a community walk on the second weekend of every month.</strong></p>
        <p>While we frequently organize additional impromptu walks and seasonal explorations throughout the month, you can always count on the second weekend of the month being blocked for a Friends of Baanaadi walk. We announce specific locations, timings, and meeting points in the days leading up to each walk.</p>

        <h2>How to Stay Updated</h2>
        <p>All upcoming walks, workshops, and community events are announced through our official channels:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Instagram:</strong> Follow our official Instagram page for upcoming walk flyers, highlight photos, and community updates.</li>
          <li><strong>WhatsApp Community:</strong> We maintain an invite-based WhatsApp group for our active members to coordinate carpools, share species checklists, and discuss sightings. You can request an invite after attending one of our walks.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What to Expect on a Walk</h2>
        <p>Our walks are slow-paced, mindful explorations focused on observing birds, listening to their calls, and appreciating their natural habitats. Here is what you should expect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>A Focus on Observation:</strong> We prioritize studying bird behavior and understanding local ecosystems.</li>
          <li><strong>Movement Over Stillness:</strong> Unlike dedicated photography outings, we keep moving to explore different niches rather than waiting in one spot for hours. While photographers are welcome, we aim to capture quick record shots rather than perfect artistic compositions.</li>
          <li><strong>Shared Learning:</strong> Experienced members are always happy to help beginners learn identification techniques and navigate field guides or apps like eBird and Merlin.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="action-box">
          <h3>Ready to walk with us?</h3>
          <p>Follow us on Instagram to stay updated on our next nature walk.</p>
          <a href={INSTAGRAM_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn">Follow Friends of Baanaadi on Instagram</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-3xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: var(--color-accent-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .content-wrapper h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .content-wrapper h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .content-wrapper p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .content-wrapper ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .content-wrapper li {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .content-wrapper li strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .action-box {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .action-box h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-accent-primary);
  }
  
  .action-box p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .sub-section {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-primary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }

  .sub-section h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .sub-section p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
  }
</style>
